 by Nesvorn\u00fd et al. In their Table 2 the reference is to the 1995 film, \"[[GoldenEye]]\".\n</ref> || 007 || align=center | 1 || align=center | inner || align=center | ASP || \u2013 || [[9007 James Bond]] || \u2014 || {{LoMP|9007|list}}\n|-id=008 bgcolor=\"#C2FFFF\"\n| 008 || Arkesilaos family || ARK || align=center | 37 || align=center | rim || align=center | \u2013 || \u2013 || [[20961 Arkesilaos]] (Jupiter trojan) || [[:Category:Arkesilaos asteroids|cat]] || {{LoMP|20961|list}}\n|-id=009 bgcolor=\"#C2FFFF\"\n| 009 || Ennomos family || ENM || align=center | 30 || align=center | rim || align=center | \u2013 || 0.06 || [[4709 Ennomos]] (Jupiter trojan) || [[:Category:Ennomos asteroids|cat]] || {{LoMP|4709|list}}\n|-id=010 bgcolor=\"#C2FFFF\"\n| 010 || ''unnamed family'' || 010 || align=center | 13 || align=center | rim || align=center | \u2013 || 0.09 || {{mpl|(247341) 2001 UV|209}} (Jupiter trojan) || \u2014 || {{LoMP|247341|list}}\n|-id=401\n| 401 || [[Vesta family]] || V || align=center | 15252 || align=center | [[Kirkwood gap|inner]] || align=center | [[V-type asteroid|V]] || 0.35 || [[4 Vesta]] (adj. Vestian) || [[:Category:Vesta asteroids|cat]] || {{LoMP|4|list}}\n|-id=402\n| 402 || [[Flora family]]<br />{{small|(Ariadne family)}} || FLO || align=center | 13786 || align=center | inner || align=center | [[S-type asteroid|S]] || 0.30 || [[8 Flora]] (adj. Florian), also named after [[43&nbsp;Ariadne]]; typical [[asteroid clan]]. Not a legitimate asteroid family according to Carruba and Milani, instead, the Florian core region is labelled Belgica family and '''Duponta family''' {{LoMP|1338|(1338)}}, respectively.<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Carruba-2013\" /> || [[:Category:Flora asteroids|cat]] || {{LoMP|8|list}}\n|-id=403\n| 403 || [[Baptistina family]] || BAP || align=center | 2500 || align=center | inner || align=center | [[X-type asteroid|X]] || 0.16 || [[298 Baptistina]], merges with the '''Belgica family''' {{LoMP|1052|(1052)}} at 100&nbsp;m/