onding wiki-category lists a total of [[:Category:Cybele asteroids|32 members]]. Not a listed family in HCM by Zappal\u00e0 (1995), Nesvorn\u00fd (2014) and [https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=5 AstDyS-2] ([https://newton.spacedys.com/~astdys2/propsynth/all_tro.famrec Src]), where these bodies are predominantly assigned to the background population.<ref name=\"Zappala-family\" /><ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />\n|- id=\"Dejanira family\"\n| Dejanira family || [[157 Dejanira]] || [[:Category:Dejanira asteroids|cat]] || Micro-family with 5 members as per Zappal\u00e0 (1995). All members: {{LoMP|157|(157)}}, {{LoMP|2290|(2290)}}, {{LoMP|5276|(5276)}}, {{LoMP|10779|(10779)}} and {{LoMP|17377|(17377)}}.<ref name=\"Zappala-family\" /> All belong to the background population according to Nesvorn\u00fd (2014).<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />\n|- id=\"Devine\"\n| Devine family || [[3561 Devine]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 19 members.\n|- id=\"Duponta\"\n| Duponta family || [[1338 Duponta]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 133 members.\n|- id=\"Epeios family\"\n|| Epeios family || [[2148 Epeios]] || \u2014 || Jupiter trojan family according to [[Fernando Roig (astronomer)|Roig]] and [[Ricardo Gil-Hutton|Gil-Hutton]] (2008). Part of the [[Menelaus clan]].<ref name=\"Roig-2008\" />\n|- id=\"Eumelos family\"\n|| Eumelos family || [[5436 Eumelos]] || \u2014 || Jupiter trojan family according to Roig and Gil-Hutton (2008). Part of the Menelaus clan.<ref name=\"Roig-2008\" />\n|- id=\"Euryalos family\"\n|| Euryalos family || [[4007 Euryalos]] || \u2014 || Jupiter trojan family according to Roig and Gil-Hutton (2008). Part of the Menelaus clan.<ref name=\"Roig-2008\" />\n|- id=\"Fa\u00efna family\"\n| Fa\u00efna family || [[751 Fa\u00efna]] || [[:Category:Fa\u00efna asteroids|cat]] || [[C-type asteroid|Carbonaceous]] family with 12 identified members as per Zappal\u00e0 (1995).<ref name=\"Zappala-family\" /> All members: {{LoMP|751|(751)}}, {{LoMP|2089|(2089)}}, {{LoMP|2420|(2420)}}, {{LoMP|3637|(3637)}}, {{LoMP|3904|(3904)}}, {{LoMP|5083|(5083)}}, {{LoMP|8087|(8087)}}, {{LoMP|10741|(10741)}}, {{LoMP|10744|(10744)}}, {{LoMP|11497|(11497)}}, {{LoMP|12975|(12975)}} and {{LoMP|29086|(29086)}}. Predominantly background population with 3 bodies belonging to the stony [[Maria family]] per Nesvorn\u00fd (2014). Not a listed family at AstDyS-2 ([https://newton.spacedys.com/~astdys2/propsynth/all_tro.famrec Src])\n|- id=\"Griqua group\"\n| [[Griqua group]] || [[1362 Griqua]] || [[:Category:Griqua asteroids|cat]] || Griqua group (not a collisional family) described by [https://www.projectpluto.com/mp_group.htm#griqua projectpluto.com]. A marginally unstable group of asteroids observed in the 2 :1 resonance with Jupiter.\n|- id=\"Hanskya\"\n| Hanskya family || [[1118 Hanskya]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 116 members.\n|- id=\"Haumea family\"\n| [[Haumea family]] || [[Haumea (dwarf planet)]] || [[:Category:Haumea family|cat]] || This is a [[Trans-Neptunian Object|TNO]]-family. As of 2017, and current categorization, the family consists of [[:Category:Haumea family|10 members]] (including parent body).{{ref label|familylist|D|}}\n|- id=\"Helio\"\n| Helio family || [[895 Helio]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 50 members.\n|- id=\"Hestia family\"\n| Hestia family || [[46 Hestia]] || [[:Category:Hestia asteroids|cat]] || Nesvorn\u00fd moved family (formerly FIN 503) to candidate status, and {{LoMP|46|(46)}} to background.<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />{{rp|19}} Also background according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 ([https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.6&n=46 AstDyS-2]).\n|- id=\"Higson\"\n| Higson family || [[3025 Higson]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 17 members.\n|- id=\"Hippasos\"\n| Hippasos family || [[17492 Hippasos]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 7 members.\n|- id=\"Huberta\"\n| Huberta family || [[260 Huberta]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 26 members. Nesvorn\u00fd moved family to candidate status.<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />{{rp|19}}\n|- id=\"Kalchas family\"\n|| Kalchas family || [[4138 Kalchas]] || \u2014 || Jupiter trojan family according to [[Fernando Roig (astronomer)|Roig]] and [[Ricardo Gil-Hutton|Gil-Hutton]] (2008). Part of the [[Menelaus clan]].<ref name=\"Roig-2008\" />\n|- id=\"Laodica family\"\n| Laodica family || [[507 Laodica]] || [[:Category:Laodica asteroids|cat]] || Category with [[:Category:Laodica asteroids|2 members]]. 507&nbsp;Laodica and [[635&nbsp;Vundtia]] are core members of the [[Eos family]] according to AstDyS-2 ([https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.6&n=507 507]; [https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.6&n=635 635]) and background asteroid per Nesvorn\u00fd ({{LoMP|507|507}}; {{LoMP|635|635}}), respectively.<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />\n|- id=\"Levin\"\n| Levin family || [[2076 Levin]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 1534 members.\n|- id=\"Liberatrix family\"\n| Liberatrix family || [[125 Liberatrix]] || [[:Category:Liberatrix asteroids|cat]] || 3 listed members. 125 Liberatrix is a background asteroid according to [https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.6&n=125 AstDyS-2], and a member of the [[Nemesis family]] according to {{LoMP|125|Nesvorn\u00fd}}.<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" /> Background asteroid: [[301&nbsp;Bavaria]] (both [https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.6&n=301 AstDyS-2] and {{LoMP|301|Nesvorn\u00fd}}). [[9923&nbsp;Ronaldthiel]] is a core member of the [[Agnia family]] at [https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.6&n=9923 AstDyS-2].\n|- id=\"Makhaon family\"\n|| Makhaon family || [[3063 Makhaon]] || \u2014 || Jupiter trojan family according to [[Fernando Roig (astronomer)|Roig]] and [[Ricardo Gil-Hutton|Gil-Hutton]] (2008). Part of the [[Menelaus clan]].<ref name=\"Roig-2008\" />\n|- id=\"Marsili\"\n| Marsili family || [[40134 Marsili]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 16 members.\n|- id=\"Martes family\"\n| Martes family || [[5026 Martes]] || [[:Category:Martes asteroids|cat]] || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 481 members. Largest asteroids are members of the [[Erigone family]] according to Nesvorn\u00fd ({{LoMP|5026|5026}}; {{LoMP|9879|9879}}).<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />\n|- id=\"Matterania\"\n| Matterania family || [[883 Matterania]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 169 members.\n|- id=\"Mecklenburg\"\n| Mecklenburg family || [[6124 Mecklenburg]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 78 members.\n|- id=\"Melanthios family\"\n|| Melanthios family || [[12973 Melanthios]] || \u2014 || Jupiter trojan family according to [[Fernando Roi