 (not a collisional family) described by [https://www.projectpluto.com/mp_group.htm#griqua projectpluto.com]. A marginally unstable group of asteroids observed in the 2 :1 resonance with Jupiter.\n|- id=\"Hanskya\"\n| Hanskya family || [[1118 Hanskya]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 116 members.\n|- id=\"Haumea family\"\n| [[Haumea family]] || [[Haumea (dwarf planet)]] || [[:Category:Haumea family|cat]] || This is a [[Trans-Neptunian Object|TNO]]-family. As of 2017, and current categorization, the family consists of [[:Category:Haumea family|10 members]] (including parent body).{{ref label|familylist|D|}}\n|- id=\"Helio\"\n| Helio family || [[895 Helio]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 50 members.\n|- id=\"Hestia family\"\n| Hestia family || [[46 Hestia]] || [[:Category:Hestia asteroids|cat]] || Nesvorn\u00fd moved family (formerly FIN 503) to candidate status, and {{LoMP|46|(46)}} to background.<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />{{rp|19}} Also background according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 ([https://newton.spacedys.com/astdys/index.php?pc=1.1.6&n=46 AstDyS-2]).\n|- id=\"Higson\"\n| Higson family || [[3025 Higson]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 17 members.\n|- id=\"Hippasos\"\n| Hippasos family || [[17492 Hippasos]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 7 members.\n|- id=\"Huberta\"\n| Huberta family || [[260 Huberta]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 26 members. Nesvorn\u00fd moved f