14 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 56 members.\n|- id=\"Univermoscow\"\n| Univermoscow family || [[6355 Univermoscow]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to Milani and Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 13 members.\n|- id=\"Zhvanetskij\"\n| Zhvanetskij family || [[5931 Zhvanetskij]] || \u2014 || MBA-family (AstDys) according to [[Andrea Milani (mathematician)|Milani]] and [[Zoran Kne\u017eevi\u0107 (astronomer)|Kne\u017eevi\u0107]] (2014).<ref name=\"Milani-2014\" /><ref name=\"Knezevic-2014\" /> Total of 23 members.\n|-\n| colspan=5 style=\"padding: 4px;\" | '''Legend''':\n*'''{{note label|familylist|C|}}''' These are families listed as \"robustly\" identified in Bendjoya and Zappala (2002). \n*'''{{note label|familylist|D|}}''' TNOs are not considered asteroids, but are included here for completeness.\n* ''' Candidate families''' (Nesvorn\u00fd):<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\" />{{rp|19}} [[929 Algunde]], [[1296 Andr\u00e9e]], [[1646 Rosseland]], [[1942 Jablunka]], [[2007 McCuskey]], [[2409 Chapman]], [[4689 Donn]], [[6246 Komurotoru]]. {{mp|(13698) 1998 KF|35}}, [[539 Pamina]], {{mpl|(300163) 2006 VW|139}}, [[3567 Alvema]], {{mpl|(7744) 1986 QA|1}} [[260 Huberta]], [[928 Hildrun]], [[2621 Goto]], [[1113 Katja]], [[8737 Takehiro]], [[46 Hestia]] [[5 Astraea]], [[1044 Teutonia]], [[3110 Wagman]], [[4945 Ikenozenni]], {{mpl|(7744) 1986 QA|1}}, [[8905 Bankakuko]], {{mpl|(25315) 1999 AZ|8}}, {{mp|(28804) 2000 HC|81}}.\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Proper orbital elements]]\n* [[:Category:Asteroid groups and families]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"Nesvorny-2014\">{{Cite journal\n  |first1     = D. |last1 = Nesvorn\u00fd\n  |first2     = M. |last2 = Broz\n  |first3     = V. |last3 = Carruba\n  |date       = December 2014\n  |title      = Identification and Dynamical Properties